Title: Ranco O17 O17-R4701 flared dual pressure control
Description: Certified for use as a specific safety device, this Ranco O17-R4701 adjustable dual pressure switch with 1/4" flare connection is part of an SPDT series with high capacity contacts. Switches in this range are supplied in various pressure ranges and with fittings including a solder braze tube, mechanical fitting or with capillary and switch action. Suitable for use in commercial applications, O16 switches control refrigeration cabinets and chillers or can be used as safety cut-outs.
category: Refrigeration/Controls/Refrigeration Pressure Switches/Refrigeration Pressure Switches.csv -> Ranco O17 O17-R4701 flared dual pressure control

Title: Danfoss KP1 low pressure auto reset switch -0.2/7.5bar
Description: Designed for use in refrigeration and air conditioning systems, the Danfoss KP1 low pressure switch with 1/4" flare connection provides protection from low suction pressure or high discharge pressure. It can also be used to start and stop refrigeration compressors and fans on air-cooled condensers. Connecting directly to a single-phase AC motor up to 2kW, the KP1 can alternatively be installed in the control circuit of DC or large AC motors. This device is fitted with a SPDT switch, its position determined by the pressure switch setting and pressure at the connector.

Title: Henry Technologies 5231 pressure relief valve 24.8bar 1/2x5/8" (ce ped)
Description: Protecting refrigeration systems against over-pressure, this Henry Technologies 5231 pressure relief valve (PRV) has 1/2" NPTF x 5/8" SAE flare connections. Description: Designed to protect refrigeration systems, the Eliwell NSD high pressure switch with 1/4" flare connection works via the setting of high or low pressure limits.
